listAlternativeRanges

public java.util.Iterator listAlternativeRanges(boolean activeClassOnly)
Return an an interator or Resources that represent additional ranges for this property. The activeClassOnly flag determines if we consider only those restrictions declared in the active class

listAllRanges

public java.util.Iterator listAllRanges()
Return an an interator or Resources that represent all possible ranges for this property gathered from the entire hierarchy. An element in the iterator will be a special Resource indicating the default return type. As such, the items in the Iterator may be used in calls to getReturnType(), getPropertyName(), and getPropertyCapped() but should not be treated as verbatim.

listAllRanges

public java.util.Iterator listAllRanges(boolean activeClassOnly)
Return an an interator or Resources that represent all possible ranges for this property. the boolean parameter indicates whether we should include return types declared in the activeClass only or in the entire hiearchy. The active class is the class we are generating for.
